<TITLE> Tractor rams vehicles in Jerusalem, driver shot </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 JERUSALEM, Thu Mar 5,(bdnews24.com/Reuters) - The driver of a bulldozer was shot after he slammed it into an empty bus and a police car on a busy Jerusalem roadway on Thursday, police said. "It seems to be a terrorist attack from the evidence we have at the moment," police spokesman Mickey Rosenfeld said, though he offered no specifics. Rosenfeld said policemen fired at the driver of the bulldozer after it turned over a police car and hit a bus, which had no passengers at the time. A Reuters witness saw the driver of the bulldozer being taken away by an ambulance. Rosenfeld said the driver had been seriously injured. Israel Radio said he was killed. Channel 10 television reported that a taxi driver at the scene shot the bulldozer driver, not the police
